and his wife.

253
00:22:41,819 --> 00:22:43,362
And your little dog too!

254
00:23:02,548 --> 00:23:03,716
Pitiful.

255
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:06,427
What? Who are you?

256
00:23:07,887 --> 00:23:10,598
Where are my manners?

257
00:23:11,307 --> 00:23:14,685
Sonic, meet Knuckles.

258
00:23:14,768 --> 00:23:16,979
My new BFFAE.

259
00:23:17,062 --> 00:23:20,441
Bestest friend forever and ever!

260
00:23:20,524 --> 00:23:23,652
Look, Robotnik, I don't care
who you brought to help you.

261
00:23:23,736 --> 00:23:25,571
You're never going to get my power.

262
00:23:25,654 --> 00:23:28,240
Do I look like I need your power?

263
00:23:38,792 --> 00:23:43,005
So nice when diabolical evil
lives up to the hype.

264
00:23:46,008 --> 00:23:47,343
Where is it?

265
00:23:47,426 --> 00:23:50,471
You want it? Here it comes.

266
00:23:50,554 --> 00:23:55,184
I was expecting more of you.
You're unskilled.

267
00:23:56,060 --> 00:23:57,311
Untrained.

268
00:23:58,854 --> 00:24:01,190
And unworthy!

269
00:24:02,650 --> 00:24:06,195
You forgot one. Unstoppable.

270
00:24:32,137 --> 00:24:35,975
It is my destiny
to do what my ancestors could not...

271
00:24:36,058 --> 00:24:40,229
To restore the ultimate power
to the home of my people.

272
00:24:41,271 --> 00:24:44,775
Ultimate power?
I don't know what you're talking about.

273
00:24:44,858 --> 00:24:46,068
You've got the wrong guy.

274
00:24:46,151 --> 00:24:48,320
Ultimate power?

275
00:24:48,821 --> 00:24:51,615
Now you're speaking my language.

276
00:24:51,699 --> 00:24:54,868
Don't play dumb with me,
apprentice of Longclaw.

277
00:24:54,952 --> 00:24:56,412
You knew Longclaw?

278
00:24:56,495 --> 00:25:00,624
Longclaw and her people were
the sworn enemy of my tribe, the Echidna.

279
00:25:00,708 --> 00:25:05,713
We fought and died at their hands,
and now you will die at mine.

280
00:25:16,390 --> 00:25:18,559
Come on. Get in! I'm on your side.

281
00:25:18,642 --> 00:25:20,561
I'm sorry. Who are you?

282
00:25:21,812 --> 00:25:23,522
You know what? It doesn't matter.

283
00:25:26,066 --> 00:25:28,110
Get us out of here! Go, go, go!

284
00:25:32,322 --> 00:25:33,323
He's gone rabid!

285
00:25:35,576 --> 00:25:36,994
Gross! Is he licking it?

286
00:25:38,203 --> 00:25:39,496
See ya!

287
00:25:39,580 --> 00:25:41,874
Make sure to get your shots, Eggman!

288
00:25:55,763 --> 00:25:59,433
Wow. Okay. Let me just say
it is an honor to finally meet you, Sonic.

289
00:25:59,516 --> 00:26:01,060
Is it okay if I call you Sonic?

290
00:26:01,143 --> 00:26:03,896
Everyone calls me Tails.
You're probably wondering why.

291
00:26:03,979 --> 00:26:06,356
Let me guess. Because of the extra tail?

292
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:08,358
That's right!
I should've known you'd get that.

293
00:26:08,442 --> 00:26:12,154
Cool. Also, what is going on?
Robotnik's back?

294
00:26:12,237 --> 00:26:14,698
And who is
Clifford the Big Red Rage Monster?

295
00:26:15,365 --> 00:26:17,326
That's Knuckles, the last of the Echidnas

296
00:26:17,409 --> 00:26:19,828
and the most dangerous warrior
in the galaxy.

297
00:26:19,912 --> 00:26:21,997
He's obsessed with finding
the Master Emerald.

298
00:26:22,081 --> 00:26:24,416
Are you serious? The Master Emerald?

299
00:26:24,500 --> 00:26:26,126
That's just a bedtime story.

300
00:26:26,210 --> 00:26:27,628
Well, he believes it's real.

301
00:26:27,711 --> 00:26:30,005
And he must think
you're the key to finding it.

302
00:26:32,216 --> 00:26:34,051
Red light! Give me the wheel!

303
00:26:34,134 --> 00:26:35,969
- Hey, what are you...
- Move your foot.

304
00:26:43,727 --> 00:26:45,020
I think we lost him.

305
00:26:52,945 --> 00:26:55,531
We did not lose him.
We definitely did not lose him!

306
00:27:00,786 --> 00:27:02,955
I've got an idea. Do you trust me?

307
00:27:03,038 --> 00:27:05,249
Of course not! I literally just met you!

308
00:27:05,332 --> 00:27:07,417
- Just let me... Come on!
- What are you doing?

309
00:27:26,395 --> 00:27:27,646
We're flying.

310
00:27:28,355 --> 00:27:30,440
Did your butt just turn into a helicopter?

311
00:27:31,817 --> 00:27:33,443
A butt-copter!

312
00:27:34,027 --> 00:27:37,364
Only Sonic the Hedgehog
could come up with something like that.

313
00:27:52,462 --> 00:27:54,631
Foxy move.

314
00:27:55,883 --> 00:27:57,926
You want something done right

315
00:27:59,219 --> 00:28:02,222
you have to hire someone
you can push around.

316
00:28:04,391 --> 00:28:05,267
All caps.

317
00:28:23,619 --> 00:28:24,912
Doctor,

318
00:28:25,829 --> 00:28:26,955
where are you?

319
00:28:33,754 --> 00:28:34,796
Freak.

320
00:28:43,055 --> 00:28:45,349
I'm sorry, folks.

321
00:28:45,432 --> 00:28:47,809
I have to close early. Everybody out!

322
00:28:47,893 --> 00:28:50,979
Everybody out.
Thank you for visiting the Mean Bean.

323
00:28:51,063 --> 00:28:53,106
All right, good night. Good night.

324
00:29:12,292 --> 00:29:13,335
He's back.

325
00:29:15,045 --> 00:29:17,047
He's back!

326
00:30:11,810 --> 00:30:14,021
That's more like it.

327
00:30:15,022 --> 00:30:17,858
I've been re-hatched!

328
00:30:29,411 --> 00:30:33,957
So, my massively metacarpaled friend,

329
00:30:34,041 --> 00:30:35,375
you mentioned

330
00:30:37,252 --> 00:30:39,254
ultimate power.

331
00:30:39,338 --> 00:30:40,339
Back at the house?

332
00:30:40,422 --> 00:30:42,049
The Master Emerald?

333
00:30:42,132 --> 00:30:43,508
It does not concern you.

334
00:30:43,592 --> 00:30:46,595
I got you off that planet
and you brought me to the hedgehog.

335
00:30:46,678 --> 00:30:48,764
We have no more use for each other.

336
00:30:48,847 --> 00:30:51,183
Well, I hate to be a contrarian, but

337
00:30:52,100 --> 00:30:53,226
I think we might.

338
00:30:54,728 --> 00:30:57,189
You think these machines
are a match for me?

339
00:30:57,272 --> 00:31:00,734
I will shatter them
like the bones from a fallen...

340
00:31:01,610 --> 00:31:02,736
They are stairs.

341
00:31:08,450 --> 00:31:12,621
You see, Earth is my turf, G.

342
00:31:13,121 --> 00:31:15,874
If you don't know how to floss,
you'll be lost without me.

343
00:31:15,957 --> 00:31:18,502
I understand nothing
of what you just said.

344
00:31:18,585 --> 00:31:22,964
I help you retrieve the Emerald,
and you use it to

345
00:31:24,257 --> 00:31:29,388
destroy the hedgehog!

346
00:31:29,971 --> 00:31:31,681
You're suggesting an alliance.

347
00:31:31,765 --> 00:31:35,894
Around here we simply
grip each other's hands tightly.

348
00:31:41,274 --> 00:31:44,903
You truculent space bumpkin!

349
00:31:44,986 --> 00:31:47,155
You've crushed my favorite hand!

350
00:31:47,823 --> 00:31:49,741
Really? My hand is uninjured.

351
00:31:50,951 --> 00:31:53,203
But I'm now convinced of your commitment.

352
00:31:53,286 --> 00:31:55,205
"goody,"

353
00:31:55,288 --> 00:31:58,792
he exclaimed,
while he reset two of his knuckles.

354
00:31:58,875 --> 00:32:01,211
I'm

355
00:32:01,294 --> 00:32:06,216
delighted to be on the same team.

356
00:32:14,141 --> 00:32:15,434
Road trip!

357
00:32:16,017 --> 00:32:18,061
I'll let you stick your nose
out the window.

358
00:32:20,272 --> 00:32:22,023
Sonic, where are we?

359
00:32:22,107 --> 00:32:24,484
Welcome to the Wade Cave.

360
00:32:24,568 --> 00:32:27,612
Which is something
I hope to someday say to a woman.

361
00:32:27,696 --> 00:32:29,364
A woman who's not my mom.

362
00:32:29,448 --> 00:32:31,408
Wade, focus.

363
00:32:31,491 --> 00:32:35,203
We need to figure out why Knuckles thinks
I'm the key to finding the Master Emerald.

364
00:32:35,287 --> 00:32:37,205
And why did he mention Longclaw?

365
00:32:37,789 --> 00:32:40,041
There must be a connection.

366
00:32:40,625 --> 00:32:42,043
Wait a minute. There is.

367
00:32:42,586 --> 00:32:46,506
Look. There's an emerald symbol
on the map Longclaw gave me.

368
00:32:46,590 --> 00:32:48,467
I never knew what it meant before.

369
00:32:49,176 --> 00:32:50,844
Something's happening.

370
00:33:03,982 --> 00:33:05,358
Longclaw?

371
00:33:05,442 --> 00:33:06,985
Hello, Sonic.

372
00:33:07,068 --> 00:33:10,447
If you're watching this,
then something has happened to me.

373
00:33:10,530 --> 00:33:13,366
And I pray
you've made it to Earth unharmed.

374
00:33:13,867 --> 00:33:18,163
This world has been chosen
for a very important reason.

375
00:33:18,246 --> 00:33:21,875
It's the secret location
of the Master Emerald.

376
00:33:24,002 --> 00:33:27,631
The Emerald has the power
to turn thoughts into reality.

377
00:33:28,131 --> 00:33:30,634
Like the Stay Puft Marshmallow Man
from Ghostbusters.

378
00:33:31,384 --> 00:33:35,472
In the wrong hands it could threaten
all life in the universe.

379
00:33:35,555 --> 00:33:38,475
Protecting the Emerald was my sacred duty.

380
00:33:38,558 --> 00:33:42,229
And now I must pass
that responsibility to you.

381
00:33:43,355 --> 00:33:46,024
This is my moment.

382
00:33:46,107 --> 00:33:49,569
Follow the map, find the Emerald,
and keep it safe.

383
00:33:50,195 --> 00:33:51,738
My dear Sonic,

384
00:33:51,821 --> 00:33:54,783
you have a heart
like no creature I've ever known.

385
00:33:55,408 --> 00:33:57,077
I love you so much.

386
00:33:58,745 --> 00:33:59,955
Goodbye.

387
00:34:01,331 --> 00:34:03,124
No, no, wait.

388
00:34:10,257 --> 00:34:12,133
I won't let you down, Longclaw.

389
00:34:14,094 --> 00:34:17,222
So is that your dad?

390
00:34:17,305 --> 00:34:18,765
What?

391
00:34:18,848 --> 00:34:19,724
No?

392
00:34:20,600 --> 00:34:23,436
According to this map,
the first clue is in Siberia.

393
00:34:23,520 --> 00:34:25,814
It's a compass
that will lead to the Emerald.

394
00:34:25,897 --> 00:34:28,817
And with Knuckles already here,
it's a race.

395
00:34:28,900 --> 00:34:29,901
Knuckles?

396
00:34:30,652 --> 00:34:32,445
I knew a kid in middle school
named Knuckles.

397
00:34:32,529 --> 00:34:34,364
Could fit his whole fist in his mouth.

398
00:34:34,447 --> 00:34:38,577
If this is the same Knuckles,
we are screwed.

399
00:34:38,660 --> 00:34:41,079
This Knuckles, that Knuckles.
It doesn't matter.

400
00:34:41,162 --> 00:34:42,831
We're gonna get there first.

401
00:34:45,834 --> 00:34:47,586
What do you mean, "we"?

402
00:34:47,669 --> 00:34:48,962
You're coming with me.

403
00:34:49,045 --> 00:34:50,380
No, no, no.

404
00:34:50,463 --> 00:34:53,675
I just came here to warn you.
I'm not a field guy.

405
00:34:53,758 --> 00:34:57,554
Don't worry. I got your back.
I won't let anything happen to you.

406
00:34:59,014 --> 00:35:02,767
It's a power bump.
On Earth, it means an unbreakable promise.

407
00:35:02,851 --> 00:35:05,562
Okay, I'm in.

408
00:35:21,286 --> 00:35:23,663
Doctor. It's really you.

409
00:35:24,581 --> 00:35:26,124
You look different.

410
00:35:26,750 --> 00:35:29,419
Papa's got a brand new 'stache.

411
00:35:32,547 --> 00:35:36,176
I knew it. I knew it!
I knew you'd come back, sir.

412
00:35:36,259 --> 00:35:38,678
I never stopped steaming
your Austrian goat's milk.

413
00:35:44,601 --> 00:35:45,935
Could use some mushroom.

414
00:35:47,812 --> 00:35:48,980
You brought something.

415
00:35:49,731 --> 00:35:52,525
Some kind of space porcupine.

416
00:35:53,026 --> 00:35:56,029
Porcupine? I am an Echidna!

417
00:35:56,112 --> 00:35:58,698
Trained since birth
in all forms of lethal combat,

418
00:35:58,782 --> 00:36:00,992
destined to restore honor to my tribe,

419
00:36:01,076 --> 00:36:04,871
and willing to destroy
anything that gets in my way.

420
00:36:05,497 --> 00:36:06,873
Welcome to the team.

421
00:36:13,088 --> 00:36:15,006
That means he trusts you, Stone.

422
00:36:15,632 --> 00:36:18,343
Now let's renovate this dump!

423
00:36:19,010 --> 00:36:21,346
Latte with steamed Austrian goat milk!

424
00:36:41,658 --> 00:36:42,909
Good one. Solid.

425
00:36:50,125 --> 00:36:51,459
- Sorry, fellas.
- That's game!

426
00:36:52,585 --> 00:36:54,212
That's how we do!

427
00:36:54,796 --> 00:36:57,173
- But are they good at math?
- Teamwork makes the dream work!

428
00:36:57,799 --> 00:36:59,134
Sorry about that, Big Tom.

429
00:36:59,759 --> 00:37:01,803
- Are you good?
- All good. Fine.

430
00:37:01,886 --> 00:37:04,931
Thanks for inviting me out to hang
with you and your groomsmen.

431
00:37:05,014 --> 00:37:06,516
Good quality bonding.

432
00:37:07,142 --> 00:37:08,309
You know, bro,

433
00:37:08,393 --> 00:37:10,895
those guys right there,
they're way more than my groomsmen.

434
00:37:10,979 --> 00:37:12,105
That's my squad.

435
00:37:12,188 --> 00:37:14,232
Never would've made it through life
without 'em.

436
00:37:14,315 --> 00:37:15,358
Get over here!

437
00:37:15,442 --> 00:37:17,152
Yeah, I'm coming!

438
00:37:17,736 --> 00:37:20,447
- I'll catch you later.
- Hey. Yeah!

439
00:37:20,530 --> 00:37:22,824
Let me know if you're ready
for some power yoga.

440
00:37:22,907 --> 00:37:25,952
- You bet.
- Come on, Tommy boy. Let's go.

441
00:37:26,035 --> 00:37:27,078
Don't make me.

442
00:37:28,163 --> 00:37:29,247
What am I doing?

443
00:37:29,330 --> 00:37:30,623
Hey, Uncle Tommy!

444
00:37:30,707 --> 00:37:32,208
Hey, girls!

445
00:37:32,292 --> 00:37:35,128
How you do... Are those the wedding rings?

446
00:37:35,712 --> 00:37:36,713
May I?

447
00:37:36,796 --> 00:37:40,258
This little ring bearer
has been taking her job very seriously.

448
00:37:40,341 --> 00:37:42,677
- She's been practicing all morning.
- I can see that.

449
00:37:42,761 --> 00:37:45,138
How very responsible of you.

450
00:37:45,221 --> 00:37:46,890
Except aren't there supposed
to be two wedding rings?

451
00:37:49,893 --> 00:37:53,313
- Uncle Tommy?
- Hang on. What's going on here?

452
00:37:55,732 --> 00:37:56,941
You're gonna do great, kiddo.

453
00:37:57,025 --> 00:37:58,067
Bye.

454
00:37:58,151 --> 00:37:59,527
- Hey, baby.
- Hi.

455
00:38:02,655 --> 00:38:04,657
That's right! Groom in the building!

456
00:38:04,741 --> 00:38:06,201
Look at those guys.

457
00:38:06,785 --> 00:38:08,203
I wish Sonic had that.

458
00:38:08,745 --> 00:38:10,955
- Muscles?
- Control yourself.

459
00:38:12,040 --> 00:38:15,668
No. Buddies. Wingmen. A squad.

460
00:38:15,752 --> 00:38:19,255
Sonic doesn't have anything like that.
He's flying solo.

461
00:38:20,131 --> 00:38:22,091
Baby, you got to relax.

462
00:38:22,175 --> 00:38:24,385
You're at the Four Seasons.

463
00:38:24,469 --> 00:38:27,388
Have a mai tai.
Spend some time with your wife.

464
00:38:27,472 --> 00:38:30,558
That's what he said.
Seriously, his exact words.

465
00:38:30,642 --> 00:38:34,687
See? He's a smart kid. He'll find his way.

466
00:38:35,271 --> 00:38:38,358
I absolutely cannot find my way.

467
00:38:38,441 --> 00:38:41,778
We are completely, totally,
unequivocally lost.

468
00:38:43,238 --> 00:38:44,697
Sonic, in this weather,

469
00:38:44,781 --> 00:38:47,784
there's no way we're gonna get
any readings on this thing!

470
00:38:47,867 --> 00:38:49,619
- Should we go back?
- No, no, no.

471
00:38:49,702 --> 00:38:52,956
There's a light up ahead.
Maybe we can take shelter in there.

472
00:38:58,545 --> 00:38:59,629
Perfect.

473
00:38:59,712 --> 00:39:02,882
Are you sure about this?
We don't know who's inside.

474
00:39:02,966 --> 00:39:06,219
Don't worry.
On Earth, people are very welcoming,

475
00:39:06,302 --> 00:39:09,681
and love taking complete strangers
into their homes.

476
00:39:39,836 --> 00:39:40,795
Run.

477
00:39:43,423 --> 00:39:45,008
Table for two, please!

478
00:39:47,135 --> 00:39:49,345
What would you like to order?

479
00:39:49,429 --> 00:39:51,139
Two beef stews, please.

480
00:39:56,603 --> 00:39:59,772
- Where'd you get all these cool gadgets?
- I invented 'em.

481
00:39:59,856 --> 00:40:01,774
That's kinda my thing.

482
00:40:01,858 --> 00:40:04,319
In fact,
my inventions are how I discovered you.

483
00:40:05,153 --> 00:40:07,488
Remember that night at the baseball field?

484
00:40:07,572 --> 00:40:11,284
Your energy blast reached all the way
to my home planet.

485
00:40:11,367 --> 00:40:15,997
I saw you save your whole village
from that crazy mustache guy.

486
00:40:16,080 --> 00:40:19,292
Wait, so you've been watching me
this whole time?

487
00:40:19,375 --> 00:40:20,960
Even in the shower?

488
00:40:21,044 --> 00:40:22,962
That's a trick question.

489
00:40:23,046 --> 00:40:25,256
Sonic the Hedgehog prefers bubble baths.

490
00:40:25,340 --> 00:40:26,674
Man, you're good!

491
00:40:26,758 --> 00:40:29,218
When I learned Knuckles was on your trail,

492
00:40:29,302 --> 00:40:32,138
I knew I couldn't just sit back
and watch anymore.

493
00:40:32,221 --> 00:40:33,681
I had to come warn you.

494
00:40:34,933 --> 00:40:36,601
What? Hang on one sec.

495
00:40:36,684 --> 00:40:38,269
Donut Lord is checking in.

496
00:40:40,355 --> 00:40:43,900
"Just chilling. Watching TV."

497
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:46,152
Dot, dot, dot.

498
00:40:46,861 --> 00:40:48,988
Dot, dot, dot.

499
00:40:49,739 --> 00:40:51,449
Dot, dot, dot.

500
00:40:51,532 --> 00:40:53,326
Dot, dot, dot.

501
00:40:53,910 --> 00:40:56,496
Dot, dot, dot.

502
00:40:56,996 --> 00:40:57,997
Doctor,

503
00:40:58,998 --> 00:41:01,334
why are we working with this imbecile?

504
00:41:02,669 --> 00:41:07,256
Because that simpleminded space trash
is the key to something extraordinary.

505
00:41:08,174 --> 00:41:10,718
Something to help you get revenge
on the hedgehog.

506
00:41:11,219 --> 00:41:12,428
Think bigger, Stone.

507
00:41:13,012 --> 00:41:16,307
The emerald he seeks
could power my wildest designs.

508
00:41:16,391 --> 00:41:18,768
My genius wouldn't just be recognized
on Earth.

