01:02:04,179 --> 01:02:06,348
Okay, let me think. Tails, come on, buddy.

766
01:02:11,102 --> 01:02:12,479
Hey!

767
01:02:12,562 --> 01:02:14,731
Randall, why do all of your friends
have weapons?

768
01:02:16,816 --> 01:02:20,070
You really should have taken me up
on that brunch, Mr. and Mrs. Wachowski.

769
01:02:20,862 --> 01:02:21,905
Olive Garden guy?

770
01:02:21,988 --> 01:02:24,532
It's okay, everyone. We're federal agents.

771
01:02:25,909 --> 01:02:27,786
You, too, Agent. Go ahead.

772
01:02:34,292 --> 01:02:38,380
You mean to tell me
that this entire wedding was a setup?

773
01:02:38,463 --> 01:02:40,173
- Rachel, wait a minute.
- What?

774
01:02:40,257 --> 01:02:41,341
That's correct, ma'am.

775
01:02:41,424 --> 01:02:44,803
Every single aspect of Operation Catfish
was a complete fabrication.

776
01:02:45,971 --> 01:02:47,389
Operation Catfish?

777
01:02:48,181 --> 01:02:49,766
So is everyone here an agent?

778
01:02:51,226 --> 01:02:52,394
Are you an agent?

779
01:02:53,228 --> 01:02:54,396
Son of a...

780
01:02:54,896 --> 01:02:58,233
Was the florist an agent?
How about the photographer?

781
01:02:58,858 --> 01:03:00,360
The woman who waxed my

782
01:03:01,361 --> 01:03:02,445
at the spa?

783
01:03:04,447 --> 01:03:06,449
- Is Jojo an agent?
- Rachel.

784
01:03:07,117 --> 01:03:09,119
- What?
- Rachel, listen to me.

785
01:03:09,202 --> 01:03:12,289
I'm done listening! I am done listening!

786
01:03:12,831 --> 01:03:15,834
I am so sorry. I am so sorry.

787
01:03:15,917 --> 01:03:17,502
I really am. I am so sorry.

788
01:03:19,462 --> 01:03:21,131
No. Hey, no!

789
01:03:22,507 --> 01:03:24,676
Let him go! Hey!

790
01:03:27,637 --> 01:03:28,805
Sonic, hang on.

791
01:03:29,848 --> 01:03:31,975
- Take it easy. It's not worth it.
- Tom!

792
01:03:32,892 --> 01:03:35,478
Sonic is not a threat. He's on our side.

793
01:03:35,562 --> 01:03:37,480
He's an uncontrolled extraterrestrial.

794
01:03:37,564 --> 01:03:39,649
And your days of aiding
and abetting him are over.

795
01:03:40,400 --> 01:03:42,444
Secure them in the hotel
until the chopper arrives.

796
01:03:43,194 --> 01:03:44,446
You're making a mistake.

797
01:03:44,529 --> 01:03:46,072
Hold on, Major A-hole!

798
01:03:46,740 --> 01:03:48,325
This is still my day,

799
01:03:48,408 --> 01:03:52,120
and someone is gonna explain to me
what the hell is going on here!

800
01:03:52,203 --> 01:03:55,540
After the events in San Francisco,
a global task force was created,

801
01:03:55,623 --> 01:03:58,835
devoted to protecting our planet
from alien threats.

802
01:03:58,918 --> 01:04:01,588
That day,
Guardian Units of Nations was born.

803
01:04:01,671 --> 01:04:04,257
- G-U-N. Seriously?
- GUN, yeah.

804
01:04:04,341 --> 01:04:06,926
Look, what about protecting our planet
from Dr. Robotnik?

805
01:04:08,261 --> 01:04:09,637
Robotnik is dead.

806
01:04:09,721 --> 01:04:11,806
You're wrong. He's back.

807
01:04:11,890 --> 01:04:14,309
And you just hauled away the only ones
who could stop him.

808
01:04:17,354 --> 01:04:19,064
Sounds like Robotnik
might be back in play.

809
01:04:19,147 --> 01:04:21,649
If he is, I want him found immediately.

810
01:04:22,984 --> 01:04:25,153
And cancel my five o'clock
at the Olive Garden.

811
01:04:25,653 --> 01:04:27,280
- Aunt Maddie?
- Yeah.

812
01:04:27,364 --> 01:04:29,032
Sonic and his friend dropped this.

813
01:04:35,872 --> 01:04:37,290
I have an idea.

814
01:04:37,374 --> 01:04:39,542
And I want to have a word with my fiancé.

815
01:04:39,626 --> 01:04:41,252
And that word is "murder."

816
01:04:46,716 --> 01:04:48,760
Hey, come on.
You can't just leave us in here.

817
01:04:48,843 --> 01:04:51,971
My friend is hurt!
He needs a doctor, a vet, anyone!

818
01:04:53,390 --> 01:04:56,184
Tails, you got to wake up, buddy.
Please wake up.

819
01:05:04,526 --> 01:05:05,652
All clear.

820
01:05:09,280 --> 01:05:10,865
All right. Game plan.

821
01:05:10,949 --> 01:05:13,910
I get inside the hotel and find
where they're hiding Tom and Sonic.

822
01:05:13,993 --> 01:05:15,620
Then I find Randall, right?

823
01:05:15,703 --> 01:05:17,122
And then I squeeze the breath

824
01:05:17,205 --> 01:05:21,292
from his lying, deceitful,
perfectly manscaped body!

825
01:05:23,670 --> 01:05:25,380
I'm going through a lot right now.

826
01:05:25,463 --> 01:05:28,550
- So let me process this my own way, okay?
- Sure, sure.

827
01:05:29,217 --> 01:05:30,844
- No judgment.
- Should've brought a journal.

828
01:05:30,927 --> 01:05:32,303
Okay...

829
01:05:32,387 --> 01:05:35,932
Okay. Is this meant to be a weapon?
This is adorable.

830
01:05:37,100 --> 01:05:38,143
Take that, Randall!

831
01:05:39,060 --> 01:05:40,270
Run, Randall!

832
01:05:40,353 --> 01:05:41,771
All right.

833
01:05:41,855 --> 01:05:43,773
- We're about to find out.
- All right!

834
01:05:43,857 --> 01:05:45,650
Let's go kick some booty.

835
01:05:59,164 --> 01:06:00,623
Rachel! No. Rachel!

836
01:06:01,916 --> 01:06:03,001
In a minute.

837
01:06:08,715 --> 01:06:09,674
Stop right there!

838
01:06:10,383 --> 01:06:11,593
Get the bag.

839
01:06:19,809 --> 01:06:21,352
He's gonna come back down, right?

840
01:06:21,436 --> 01:06:22,896
I don't know.

841
01:06:22,979 --> 01:06:23,980
Good luck!

842
01:06:26,149 --> 01:06:28,485
Look. Tom and Sonic have to be inside.

843
01:06:29,194 --> 01:06:30,987
I got a fiancé to vaporize.

844
01:06:31,070 --> 01:06:32,572
- Watch your back, sis.
- Okay.

845
01:06:35,450 --> 01:06:36,451
Randall!

846
01:06:44,083 --> 01:06:46,127
We got her. Move in.

847
01:06:50,548 --> 01:06:51,591
Okay.

848
01:07:07,232 --> 01:07:09,150
I did not mean to do that!

849
01:07:21,913 --> 01:07:23,873
Something bothering you, Agent?

850
01:07:23,957 --> 01:07:26,626
I just feel a little guilty
about what I did to Rachel, sir.

851
01:07:27,752 --> 01:07:30,004
Don't worry about it.
We'll send her a gift card.

852
01:07:30,088 --> 01:07:32,215
Now, I propose a toast.

853
01:07:35,426 --> 01:07:38,221
To a perfectly executed operation.

854
01:07:42,892 --> 01:07:44,561
Sir, we're under attack.

855
01:08:04,956 --> 01:08:08,459
Randall, wifey's home!

856
01:08:13,131 --> 01:08:14,757
My God. Rachel.

857
01:08:39,449 --> 01:08:42,285
What a woman.

858
01:08:44,454 --> 01:08:45,663
You no-good,

859
01:08:46,914 --> 01:08:49,917
lowdown, dirty, lying

860
01:08:50,001 --> 01:08:51,210
Rachel, just listen to me.

861
01:08:51,294 --> 01:08:55,548
What kind of twisted sicko
tricks someone into a fake wedding?

862
01:08:57,967 --> 01:09:00,178
Party's over, Bridezilla.
Stop right there.

863
01:09:01,512 --> 01:09:03,640
You son of a...

864
01:09:03,723 --> 01:09:05,266
- Have it your way.
- No!

865
01:09:05,975 --> 01:09:07,602
No!

866
01:09:12,523 --> 01:09:14,859
Very disappointing, Agent Handel.

867
01:09:17,779 --> 01:09:21,199
- Is that supposed to be a weapon?
- I don't know, but we gonna find out.

868
01:09:21,282 --> 01:09:23,701
Haven't you caused enough trouble
for one day?

869
01:09:23,785 --> 01:09:26,079
I haven't even begun causing trouble.

870
01:09:26,746 --> 01:09:29,874
Hell hath no fury like a bride scorned.

871
01:09:36,714 --> 01:09:39,008
Looks like it's real?

872
01:09:43,262 --> 01:09:44,597
No. Right.

873
01:09:46,516 --> 01:09:49,102
Be honest. How bad is it?

874
01:09:49,686 --> 01:09:52,313
Not bad at all.
You got Tased. You'll be fine.

875
01:09:56,901 --> 01:10:00,321
- I'm so cold.
- You landed on our ice sculpture.

876
01:10:00,405 --> 01:10:01,489
Get up.

877
01:10:09,205 --> 01:10:12,083
Just tell me the truth, for once.

878
01:10:13,251 --> 01:10:17,422
Is there anything about you
or about us that was real?

879
01:10:18,214 --> 01:10:21,551
Rachel, look at me.

880
01:10:22,885 --> 01:10:26,514
Before I met you, I didn't think
that I was even capable of real happiness.

881
01:10:28,182 --> 01:10:30,435
But that all changed
when you walked into my life.

882
01:10:31,561 --> 01:10:34,313
And I ended up breaking the first rule
of undercover work.

883
01:10:35,022 --> 01:10:36,399
Which is?

884
01:10:37,150 --> 01:10:38,526
Never fall in love.

885
01:10:51,706 --> 01:10:54,375
- Maddie!
- We're busting out of here.

886
01:10:54,459 --> 01:10:55,668
How'd you get past the guards?

887
01:10:55,752 --> 01:10:57,587
Because that little fox
is into some crazy stuff.

888
01:10:57,670 --> 01:10:58,713
Come on.

889
01:11:00,298 --> 01:11:01,841
- Let's go.
- You're amazing.

890
01:11:12,643 --> 01:11:15,313
The Owls were fools to think
they could hide this.

891
01:11:53,768 --> 01:11:54,936
What's happening?

892
01:11:56,562 --> 01:11:58,231
Wait for it.

893
01:12:09,784 --> 01:12:12,036
Yes. Eureka!

894
01:12:13,246 --> 01:12:14,956
I've found it!

895
01:12:34,433 --> 01:12:35,560
Sonic.

896
01:12:37,520 --> 01:12:39,272
- What is that?
- A big problem.

897
01:12:40,314 --> 01:12:42,233
The compass led Robotnik to the Emerald.

898
01:12:42,316 --> 01:12:44,318
That's got to be hundreds of miles away.

899
01:12:45,778 --> 01:12:49,198
All right. Huddle up.
Let's figure out a plan.

900
01:12:49,282 --> 01:12:51,325
- Together.
- There's no time for that.

901
01:12:51,409 --> 01:12:53,369
I'm the only one
that can get there fast enough.

902
01:12:53,452 --> 01:12:56,330
Sonic, this is way too big for you
to do by yourself.

903
01:12:56,914 --> 01:12:58,416
You see that little fox over there?

904
01:12:59,000 --> 01:13:02,003
He came all the way across the universe
to meet his hero.

905
01:13:02,086 --> 01:13:05,006
And what did his hero do?
I practically got him killed.

906
01:13:05,882 --> 01:13:07,842
You know what? You were right.

907
01:13:08,384 --> 01:13:11,971
My moment came and I blew it. I'm no hero.

908
01:13:12,054 --> 01:13:13,222
- Wait.
- No.

909
01:13:13,306 --> 01:13:15,641
I'm not letting anyone else get hurt
because of me.

910
01:13:15,725 --> 01:13:17,602
I'm gonna fix this while I still can.

911
01:13:19,103 --> 01:13:20,730
Sonic!

912
01:13:20,813 --> 01:13:22,231
Sonic, wait!

913
01:13:25,067 --> 01:13:26,944
Hold on. Wait.

914
01:13:27,028 --> 01:13:29,530
- Don't move.
- Take it easy, little guy. You're hurt.

915
01:13:29,614 --> 01:13:33,284
But we have to help him.
You don't know what he's up against.

916
01:13:40,499 --> 01:13:41,876
You believe us now?

917
01:13:49,008 --> 01:13:50,092
Hey, Bob!

918
01:13:50,176 --> 01:13:51,928
Hey, Maria, how you doing?

919
01:13:55,473 --> 01:13:56,515
Working on my moves.

920
01:13:56,599 --> 01:13:59,226
Just keepin' it green.
No need to burn the fuel.

921
01:13:59,310 --> 01:14:00,311
Speaking of fuel...

922
01:14:06,734 --> 01:14:08,110
Closed?

923
01:14:09,695 --> 01:14:10,905
That doesn't seem right.

924
01:14:23,709 --> 01:14:24,752
Close.

925
01:14:29,298 --> 01:14:30,591
Yes.

926
01:14:30,675 --> 01:14:33,219
Makeover, makeover. Look at you.

927
01:14:33,302 --> 01:14:34,637
Freeze! Police!

928
01:14:36,013 --> 01:14:38,099
My God, you got robot hands.

929
01:14:38,182 --> 01:14:41,560
- No, they're gloves.
- Get 'em up. Now spread your fingers!

930
01:14:42,895 --> 01:14:45,523
Now wiggle 'em! Wiggle your digits!

931
01:14:46,983 --> 01:14:49,652
Yes! Like you just finished
a big musical number.

932
01:14:51,487 --> 01:14:53,030
Good.

933
01:14:53,114 --> 01:14:54,532
Why is there a light on your head?

934
01:14:58,452 --> 01:15:00,496
'Cause I'm the sheriff
for the weekend, pal.

935
01:15:09,630 --> 01:15:10,589
Water.

936
01:15:10,673 --> 01:15:12,550
Why did it have to be water?

937
01:15:15,970 --> 01:15:18,305
Okay, you can do this.

938
01:15:21,642 --> 01:15:23,519
I gotta go fast.

939
01:17:06,122 --> 01:17:09,458
I don't want to die like this!
It's derivative!

940
01:17:11,001 --> 01:17:12,670
Make room for Daddy!

941
01:17:20,636 --> 01:17:21,804
Two and two.

942
01:17:21,887 --> 01:17:25,141
Great! We're still bipedals, more or less.

943
01:17:28,435 --> 01:17:29,979
Fire in the hole!

944
01:17:32,189 --> 01:17:35,401
I've solved it. There is a booby trap
every seven seco...

945
01:17:42,074 --> 01:17:43,450
That was a little early.

946
01:17:44,952 --> 01:17:48,539
So glad it didn't cut off my mustache.

947
01:17:48,622 --> 01:17:51,041
Hey, Little Red Wrecking Ball.

948
01:17:51,876 --> 01:17:54,211
I know you're dying
to get your Emerald on,

949
01:17:54,295 --> 01:17:58,007
but can we be a little bit more mindful
of our surroundings?

950
01:17:58,507 --> 01:17:59,550
May I?

951
01:18:06,182 --> 01:18:08,767
In 30 feet, turn left.

952
01:18:08,851 --> 01:18:10,728
Work smarter, not harder.

953
01:18:32,166 --> 01:18:33,542
My pelvis.

954
01:18:37,922 --> 01:18:42,051
Okay, Secret Temple,
let's see what you've got.

955
01:18:50,351 --> 01:18:51,852
No, no, no! No!

956
01:18:56,565 --> 01:18:57,566
No.

957
01:18:58,734 --> 01:18:59,735
Yes!

958
01:19:05,699 --> 01:19:07,618
You have arrived at your destination.

959
01:19:07,701 --> 01:19:10,704
Wow. That really opened up the space.

960
01:19:10,788 --> 01:19:13,749
I can't even picture it
with an impenetrable wall now.

961
01:19:13,832 --> 01:19:15,751
And the rubble is always a nice touch.

962
01:19:24,969 --> 01:19:28,681
At last. The Master Emerald.

963
01:19:28,764 --> 01:19:30,015
Ultimate power.

964
01:19:30,099 --> 01:19:32,935
Soon order will be restored.

965
01:19:33,018 --> 01:19:36,355
All because of what we have done together.

966
01:19:36,438 --> 01:19:38,732
Such a lovely sentiment, Knuckles.

967
01:19:39,233 --> 01:19:41,819
I think I feel a single tear forming.

968
01:19:44,780 --> 01:19:46,031
Sadly

969
01:19:47,199 --> 01:19:51,745
you're as useful to me now
as a backstage pass to Limp Bizkit.

970
01:20:06,427 --> 01:20:07,594
Nailed it.

971
01:20:08,679 --> 01:20:12,224
This guy is always trying to spoil
a bad thing!

972
01:20:13,559 --> 01:20:16,061
You guys are here, too?
Took the long way?

973
01:20:16,145 --> 01:20:18,314
Is everything a joke to you?

974
01:20:18,397 --> 01:20:21,358
Why must you constantly interfere
with my destiny?

975
01:20:21,442 --> 01:20:25,112
Because my destiny is to protect
my friends and family.

976
01:20:25,195 --> 01:20:27,364
I think I just threw up in my mouth.

977
01:20:28,157 --> 01:20:33,370
And if you want that emerald,
you're gonna have to go through me.

978
01:20:55,642 --> 01:20:58,687
The Echidna's taking no prisoners today!

979
01:20:58,771 --> 01:21:02,524
Sonic has heart,
but will he lose the quill to live?

980
01:21:04,360 --> 01:21:08,030
I don't want to fight you,
but you're not giving me much choice.

981
01:21:14,745 --> 01:21:17,498
Too easy. Let's do this.

982
01:21:44,650 --> 01:21:49,071
Why don't you stand still
and die with honor?

983
01:21:49,154 --> 01:21:50,406
Let me think about it.

984
01:21:50,489 --> 01:21:54,159
Okay, I thought about it and I pass.

985
01:22:03,627 --> 01:22:05,087
Hi there, beautiful.

986
01:22:06,380 --> 01:22:08,382
You're the real deal, aren't you?

987
01:22:09,091 --> 01:22:12,511
Where have you been all my life?

988
01:22:16,348 --> 01:22:18,767
Say goodbye, hedgehog.

989
01:22:22,271 --> 01:22:25,190
Knuckles, stop.
Robotnik's stealing the Emerald!

990
01:22:25,274 --> 01:22:27,734
What kind of fool do you take me for?

991
01:22:27,818 --> 01:22:29,069
Just look.

992
01:22:31,613 --> 01:22:32,948
Mine.

993
01:22:34,199 --> 01:22:36,910
Wait! That wasn't the deal.

994
01:22:40,372 --> 01:22:43,000
You poor, naive creature.

995
01:22:43,083 --> 01:22:44,501
It's not your fault.

996
01:22:44,585 --> 01:22:48,213
A more advanced intellect would have seen
this move coming a mile away.

997
01:22:48,297 --> 01:22:50,132
Or 1.6 kilometers.

998
01:22:50,632 --> 01:22:53,385
But I trusted you! You were my friend!

999
01:23:00,517 --> 01:23:02,936
I'm sorry. That just hit me funny.

1000
01:23:03,854 --> 01:23:08,901
Let this be my final lesson to you,
you dim-witted celestial skin tag.

1001
01:23:09,860 --> 01:23:11,236
Friends

1002
01:23:11,320 --> 01:23:15,324
are open, honest
and vulnerable with each other.

1003
01:23:15,407 --> 01:23:17,951
Which means X squared
times the hypotenuse of Y squared,

1004
01:23:18,035 --> 01:23:20,871
divided by the absolute value
of friendship, equals

1005
01:23:21,371 --> 01:23:22,414
dookie!

1006
01:23:22,498 --> 01:23:23,749
No.

1007
01:23:31,882 --> 01:23:36,887
Chaos is power!

1008
01:23:55,197 --> 01:23:56,949
Let's get out of here!

1009
01:24:09,503 --> 01:24:10,671
Knuckles!

1010
01:24:15,133 --> 01:24:18,011
Water again? Come on!

1011
01:25:16,737 --> 01:25:20,741
- You saved me.
- Don't talk to me. I'm not in the mood.

1012
01:25:22,159 --> 01:25:26,163
How dare you attack me
in my hour of sorrow!

1013
01:25:27,039 --> 01:25:28,498
Why did you save me?

1014
01:25:30,542 --> 01:25:32,377
Because you saved me first,

1015
01:25:32,461 --> 01:25:36,131
which clearly gave you
a tactical advantage I do not understand.

1016
01:25:36,214 --> 01:25:39,843
It wasn't a tactic.
I couldn't just let you die.

1017
01:25:40,886 --> 01:25:45,599
Why? I've been trying to destroy you
since the moment we met.

1018
01:25:45,682 --> 01:25:49,603
Because being a hero
isn't about taking care of yourself.

1019
01:25:49,686 --> 01:25:53,106
It's about taking responsibility
for other people.

1020
01:25:55,400 --> 01:25:58,654
Wise words. An ancient Earth proverb?

1021
01:25:58,737 --> 01:26:01,156
No, sir,
that's a Wachowski family special.

1022
01:26:01,239 --> 01:26:03,241
I got it from a guy in a rowboat.

1023
01:26:03,992 --> 01:26:05,494
Someone who means a lot to me.

1024
01:26:07,412 --> 01:26:08,997
Wait a second. What's that sound?

1025
01:26:11,166 --> 01:26:14,670
Only Sonic the Hedgehog
needs rescuing this much.

1026
01:26:15,837 --> 01:26:17,714
That sly little fox!

1027
01:26:20,258 --> 01:26:22,594
Come on, Knucklehead. We're not beat yet.

1028
01:26:23,428 --> 01:26:25,931
On the mountain,
you told me you'd lost everything.

1029
01:26:26,556 --> 01:26:28,058
The way I did.

1030
01:26:28,141 --> 01:26:30,894
But you seem so hopeful and free.

1031
01:26:31,895 --> 01:26:35,482
How did you move forward
despite failing again?

1032
01:26:36,233 --> 01:26:39,361
And again. And again.
And again. And again.

1033
01:26:39,444 --> 01:26:43,073
Okay, I didn't fail that much.
But I didn't do this all alone.

1034
01:26:43,156 --> 01:26:45,742
I found a new family. New friends.

1035
01:26:45,826 --> 01:26:47,244
And you can too.

1036
01:26:49,538 --> 01:26:51,957
You don't have to be alone anymore.

1037
01:26:57,045 --> 01:26:59,214
Are you kidding me with that handshake?

1038
01:27:01,842 --> 01:27:03,260
I'm done playing games, pal.

1039
01:27:04,928 --> 01:27:06,680
You're gonna tell me what I want to know.

1040
01:27:09,099 --> 01:27:12,477
And I am asking you for the last time

1041
01:27:14,813 --> 01:27:17,274
what would you like on your bagel?

1042
01:27:17,357 --> 01:27:19,276
I'm not telling you anything.

1043
01:27:19,359 --> 01:27:22,279
And that is a display bagel.

1044
01:27:22,362 --> 01:27:25,574
I don't get it with you!
I mean, I've tried everything.

1045
01:27:25,657 --> 01:27:29,286
I was good cop. I was bad cop.
I was cop who offers you a bagel.

1046
01:27:29,369 --> 01:27:30,370
And nothing. It's like...

1047
01:27:30,454 --> 01:27:32,706
That is a display bagel. Wow.

1048
01:27:41,965 --> 01:27:43,717
Doctor, you're here.

1049
01:27:45,719 --> 01:27:50,390
Yes, I'm here, and yet I'm

1050
01:27:51,933 --> 01:27:53,602
not all there.

1051
01:27:53,685 --> 01:27:55,187
Sir, are you feeling okay?

1052
01:27:55,270 --> 01:27:59,399
I'm more than okay.

1053
01:28:00,025 --> 01:28:03,153
I'm upgraded.

1054
01:28:03,236 --> 01:28:06,281
Sinister 3.0.

1055
01:28:06,364 --> 01:28:10,368
My game is next level.

1056
01:28:15,457 --> 01:28:16,625
Hi.

1057
01:28:19,461 --> 01:28:25,634
I can smell the electricity in your brain.

1058
01:28:27,469 --> 01:28:29,763
You smell like a snack plate.

1059
01:28:31,181 --> 01:28:34,309
Yeah, that's fair. I had a couple today.

1060
01:28:34,851 --> 01:28:36,311
Sit down.

1061
01:28:40,982 --> 01:28:42,400
In the chair.

1062
01:28:45,612 --> 01:28:46,780
I didn't know.

1063
01:28:47,864 --> 01:28:50,951
'Cause he was in the chair,
so I didn't... Okay.

1064
01:28:51,034 --> 01:28:52,953
Sir? We have a problem.

1065
01:28:58,792 --> 01:29:01,419
- All teams in position!
- Set up a perimeter!

1066
01:29:01,920 --> 01:29:03,463
Move! Move! Move!

1067
01:29:18,603 --> 01:29:22,232
Incorrectus, my trusty barnacle.

1068
01:29:23,567 --> 01:29:26,027
After all these years,

1069
01:29:26,695 --> 01:29:28,405
what I finally got

1070
01:29:29,573 --> 01:29:31,616
is a solution.

1071
01:29:42,252 --> 01:29:44,129
- Commander.
- Status report.

1072
01:29:44,212 --> 01:29:47,591
Robotnik is in there with Stone
and a hostage. Possibly local PD.

1073
01:29:47,674 --> 01:29:51,052
I'm not saying he's dumb,
but if he is local PD,

1074
01:29:51,136 --> 01:29:52,762
this town's in a lot of trouble.

1075
01:29:53,513 --> 01:29:54,806
Wade.

1076
01:30:09,195 --> 01:30:10,196
Okay.

1077
01:30:11,156 --> 01:30:13,700
Rockin' that new spring collection, I see.

1078
01:30:13,783 --> 01:30:18,330
Well, if it isn't the Pastry King.

1079
01:30:18,413 --> 01:30:19,539
The Donut Lord.

1080
01:30:20,040 --> 01:30:21,833
A real genius would remember
the name of the guy

1081
01:30:21,917 --> 01:30:23,835
who helped kick your butt off this planet.

1082
01:30:23,919 --> 01:30:25,879
And I'll do it again if you mess
with Green Hills.

1083
01:30:26,963 --> 01:30:30,759
Congratulations on your so-temporary
sense of superiority.

1084
01:30:30,842 --> 01:30:33,178
You're finished, Robotnik!
We've taken everything.

1085
01:30:33,261 --> 01:30:35,972
Your lab, your drones, your funding!

1086
01:30:36,056 --> 01:30:39,225
Let's see how big of a man you are
without your silly little robots.

1087
01:30:40,977 --> 01:30:42,896
Would you like to see

1088
01:30:44,356 --> 01:30:46,483
how big a man I can be?

1089
01:30:57,369 --> 01:31:00,538
Welcome to the new norm.

1090
01:31:10,840 --> 01:31:12,217
My God!

1091
01:31:15,720 --> 01:31:19,432
Doctor! Take me with you!

1092
01:31:43,873 --> 01:31:45,709
He's taking everything apart.

1093
01:31:46,710 --> 01:31:48,128
He's building something.

1094
01:31:56,136 --> 01:31:58,513
That can only be one thing.

1095
01:31:58,596 --> 01:32:00,974
The fearsome power of the Emerald.

1096
01:32:01,057 --> 01:32:05,061
If that thing really turns thoughts
into power, we are in big trouble.

1097
01:32:05,145 --> 01:32:07,188
Robotnik has a lot of bad thoughts.

1098
01:32:07,272 --> 01:32:10,233
Hey, Sonic,
are you sure it was a good idea

1099
01:32:10,316 --> 01:32:11,818
bringing you-know-who aboard?

1100
01:32:11,901 --> 01:32:15,655
Knuckles isn't really a bad guy.
He's just a little mixed up.

1101
01:32:15,739 --> 01:32:17,449
I am not mixed up!

1102
01:32:17,532 --> 01:32:22,412
I have steely focus. And I'm complex.
And that's a lot for some people.

1103
01:32:23,246 --> 01:32:25,874
Hope you're not still mad
I hit you with that car.

1104
01:32:26,624 --> 01:32:28,376
I was completely uninjured.

1105
01:32:28,460 --> 01:32:31,629
And my revenge will come
when you least expect it, fox.

1106
01:33:03,078 --> 01:33:05,663
Sir, you're magnificent!

1107
01:33:05,747 --> 01:33:07,791
Thank you, sycophant.

1108
01:33:07,874 --> 01:33:10,293
Your admiration is inevitable.

1109
01:33:20,345 --> 01:33:21,805
I knew it!

1110
01:33:21,888 --> 01:33:24,390
Just like the Stay Puft Marshmallow Man.

1111
01:33:25,475 --> 01:33:27,519
World Domination playlist.

1112
01:33:40,865 --> 01:33:42,033
Fall back.

1113
01:33:43,451 --> 01:33:46,287
Fall back! Quick! Retreat!

1114
01:33:48,289 --> 01:33:50,375
How are we supposed to beat this thing?

1115
01:33:50,458 --> 01:33:51,501
We need a plan.

1116
01:33:51,584 --> 01:33:53,628
Knuckles, use your strength to...

1117
01:33:54,212 --> 01:33:56,548
Jump off the plane. Wow.

1118
01:33:56,631 --> 01:34:00,552
Okay, this is what we're gonna do.
Step 1: Light taunting.

1119
01:34:00,635 --> 01:34:02,387
Step 2: I have no idea.

1120
01:34:05,515 --> 01:34:06,683
Sonic!

1121
01:34:09,853 --> 01:34:11,813
Nice action figure, Eggman.

1122
01:34:11,896 --> 01:34:14,816
Does it do anything
or just stand there looking ugly?

1123
01:34:18,486 --> 01:34:21,156
Like a blister, he keeps coming back!

1124
01:34:22,157 --> 01:34:25,118
He's on the okay-to-kill list.
Shoot the missiles. Make a decision.

1125
01:34:25,201 --> 01:34:27,996
I need a moment, sir.
I'm trying to figure out how to do this.

1126
01:34:28,079 --> 01:34:30,165
Did you even glance at a manual?

1127
01:34:30,248 --> 01:34:32,417
- No!
- I'll do it.

1128
01:34:32,500 --> 01:34:33,918
Pardon my lightning.

1129
01:34:34,002 --> 01:34:35,879
You might want to ground yourself.

1130
01:34:39,132 --> 01:34:41,676
I'm gonna pop that thing open
like a can of chili...

1131
01:34:44,220 --> 01:34:45,680
Hang on!

1132
01:34:58,985 --> 01:35:01,237
- Yeah!
- Close one.

1133
01:35:02,030 --> 01:35:03,114
Sonic!

1134
01:35:06,868 --> 01:35:08,453
Robotnik!

1135
01:35:10,079 --> 01:35:11,539
Deceiver!

1136
01:35:11,623 --> 01:35:13,416
Die, mosquito.

1137
01:35:25,845 --> 01:35:26,846
I felt that.

1138
01:35:46,032 --> 01:35:47,492
What just happened?

1139
01:35:47,575 --> 01:35:50,828
It's the Stache Masher.
Right here in the manual.

1140
01:35:53,122 --> 01:35:55,458
Return to sender.

1141
01:36:03,049 --> 01:36:04,384
Stone?

1142
01:36:05,885 --> 01:36:10,056
Great. Next thing you know, there'll be
a report about a hostile work environment.

1143
01:36:13,142 --> 01:36:16,312
Those were our best attacks,
and they did nothing!

1144
01:36:16,396 --> 01:36:20,233
We can't beat Robotnik as long as he's got
that Emerald. He's too powerful.

1145
01:36:20,316 --> 01:36:23,403
Look, we aren't strong enough
to beat Robotnik on our own.

1146
01:36:23,486 --> 01:36:24,737
But there's three of us.

1147
01:36:24,821 --> 01:36:27,991
Your strength, your smarts and my speed.

1148
01:36:28,074 --> 01:36:29,742
Together. That's how we win.

1149
01:36:29,826 --> 01:36:34,289
So we make our stand here
on the field of battle.

1150
01:36:34,372 --> 01:36:35,748
As a team.

1151
01:36:35,832 --> 01:36:37,333
This is it.

1152
01:36:38,710 --> 01:36:41,379
This is our moment.

1153
01:36:43,423 --> 01:36:44,924
Time to fight.

1154
01:36:52,432 --> 01:36:55,852
Bad time to say this,
but I don't actually have a plan.

1155
01:36:56,853 --> 01:36:58,688
Tails, any ideas?

1156
01:36:58,771 --> 01:37:00,440
We have to find his weak spot.

1157
01:37:00,523 --> 01:37:02,150
I suggest the groin.

1158
01:37:02,233 --> 01:37:04,319
What? No. No!

1159
01:37:04,402 --> 01:37:06,988
Traditionally, yes,
the groin is the weakest spot.

1160
01:37:07,071 --> 01:37:09,115
Stop saying "groin."

1161
01:37:09,198 --> 01:37:10,992
Hedgehog!

1162
01:37:11,075 --> 01:37:12,410
Look out!

1163
01:37:15,204 --> 01:37:17,707
I know what his weak spot is. It's me.

1164
01:37:17,790 --> 01:37:19,542
I'm the groin!

1165
01:37:22,170 --> 01:37:25,131
Think about it.
I live rent-free in this dude's head.

1166
01:37:25,214 --> 01:37:27,050
So if I go out there and rile him up...

1167
01:37:27,133 --> 01:37:29,552
He'll focus on only you,
leaving himself open

1168
01:37:29,635 --> 01:37:31,888
to a flanking maneuver
from me and the fox!

1169
01:37:31,971 --> 01:37:34,724
Hedgehog,
you are a brave and noble warrior.

1170
01:37:34,807 --> 01:37:37,477
Go to your certain death with honor.

1171
01:37:37,560 --> 01:37:40,104
We're gonna have to work
on your pep talks, pal.

1172
01:37:40,188 --> 01:37:41,981
- Yeah.
- Let's go.

1173
01:37:45,693 --> 01:37:47,320
All right, mustache.

1174
01:37:47,403 --> 01:37:50,239
You want me? Come and get me.

1175
01:37:50,323 --> 01:37:53,076
You don't tell me
about coming and getting.

1176
01:37:53,159 --> 01:37:55,536
I am on the cutting edge
of coming and getting!

1177
01:37:55,620 --> 01:37:57,538
Coming, getting.

1178
01:37:57,622 --> 01:38:01,793
Coming, getting.
Coming, getting. Coming, getting.

1179
01:38:04,379 --> 01:38:06,464
You're really heavy.

1180
01:38:06,547 --> 01:38:10,385
That's because I am
one million percent muscle. Faster, fox!

1181
01:38:12,595 --> 01:38:15,765
- Go! Move, guys! Move back!
- Let's go, that's it! Go, go, go!

1182
01:38:15,848 --> 01:38:16,891
- Keep going!
- Go! Go!

1183
01:38:16,974 --> 01:38:18,851
- No, no! Stop!
- Stop the truck!

1184
01:38:18,935 --> 01:38:20,228
Tom, what happened here?

1185
01:38:21,270 --> 01:38:23,189
- You thinking what I'm thinking?
- Let's get our kid.

1186
01:38:23,272 --> 01:38:24,649
We need your truck!

1187
01:38:30,863 --> 01:38:33,074
Coming, getting.

1188
01:38:34,075 --> 01:38:36,077
Yoo-hoo!

1189
01:38:36,160 --> 01:38:38,079
So what's the plan here?

1190
01:38:38,663 --> 01:38:43,042
You gonna build a big robot house?
Get yourself a big robot wife?

1191
01:38:43,126 --> 01:38:47,463
I'm going to enslave humanity
and force them to service my machines.

1192
01:38:47,547 --> 01:38:50,383
First, Green Hills. Then the universe.

1193
01:38:50,466 --> 01:38:51,717
Then the multiverse.

1194
01:38:51,801 --> 01:38:54,512
Then who knows? Maybe that'll be enough.

1195
01:38:55,179 --> 01:38:56,472
Full disclosure?

1196
01:38:57,348 --> 01:38:59,934
You won't be there.

1197
01:39:04,480 --> 01:39:06,607
Eye lasers? Really?

1198
01:39:19,078 --> 01:39:21,038
Snot rocket!

1199
01:39:22,623 --> 01:39:23,666
No, no, no!

1200
01:39:32,175 --> 01:39:33,676
Giving up already?

1201
01:39:33,759 --> 01:39:37,472
Not so tough when you're fighting someone
700 times your size, are ya?

1202
01:39:39,599 --> 01:39:42,059
You can't beat me!

1203
01:39:42,143 --> 01:39:45,354
I'm all-powerful! All-knowing!

1204
01:39:48,065 --> 01:39:50,276
All-seeing.

1205
01:39:51,402 --> 01:39:53,738
Looks like your fancy robot has a glitch.

1206
01:39:53,821 --> 01:39:57,074
Is it me? What about me? I'm over here.
Up top! Down below! Behind you!

1207
01:39:58,075 --> 01:39:59,994
I'm over here. Sorry! Over here.

1208
01:40:00,620 --> 01:40:01,829
Too slow! Try again.

1209
01:40:01,913 --> 01:40:03,956
- You can't outsmart me.
- Missed me again.

1210
01:40:04,040 --> 01:40:05,833
I'm the outsmarter-er!

1211
01:40:10,171 --> 01:40:13,132
I didn't outsmart you.
I'm just the distraction.

1212
01:40:13,216 --> 01:40:14,509
Robotnik!

1213
01:40:15,134 --> 01:40:17,887
I am also a hologram.

1214
01:40:17,970 --> 01:40:19,889
Disloyal.

1215
01:40:19,972 --> 01:40:22,808
"Dis" is how I roll.

1216
01:40:51,212 --> 01:40:52,755
Where's my Emerald?

1217
01:40:53,506 --> 01:40:55,383
No, no, no, no!

1218
01:40:55,466 --> 01:40:57,802
Computer, auxiliary power.

1219
01:41:07,144 --> 01:41:09,397
The Emerald. It's right there.

1220
01:41:09,939 --> 01:41:11,857
Move, you hunk of junk!

1221
01:41:16,404 --> 01:41:19,782
I have to... reach it.

1222
01:41:43,014 --> 01:41:44,015
Come on.

1223
01:41:46,183 --> 01:41:48,352
There he is! Go! Go, go, go!

1224
01:41:57,278 --> 01:41:58,321
No!

1225
01:41:58,404 --> 01:41:59,697
We got you, Sonic.

1226
01:42:00,906 --> 01:42:02,325
Hold on!

1227
01:42:15,546 --> 01:42:17,798
- You guys okay?
- Yeah.

1228
01:42:19,300 --> 01:42:20,343
Okay.

1229
01:42:25,890 --> 01:42:27,933
I got the Emerald.
We could still defeat him.

1230
01:42:28,017 --> 01:42:31,187
Come on, come on.
How does this thing work? What do I do?

1231
01:42:32,396 --> 01:42:33,564
What?

1232
01:42:34,231 --> 01:42:36,942
No. No, no, no!

1233
01:42:40,821 --> 01:42:44,992
Look at the happy little family.

1234
01:42:50,873 --> 01:42:53,376
You have to get away from me.
I'm the one he wants.

1235
01:42:53,459 --> 01:42:54,460
Hey.

1236
01:42:54,960 --> 01:42:56,587
We're not going anywhere.

1237
01:42:57,171 --> 01:42:58,339
We're family.

1238
01:43:01,926 --> 01:43:03,594
And families stick together

1239
01:43:06,472 --> 01:43:07,682
no matter what.

1240
01:43:10,810 --> 01:43:11,936
I love you guys.

1241
01:43:12,853 --> 01:43:14,397
We love you too, Sonic.

1242
01:43:22,905 --> 01:43:24,365
No!

1243
01:43:26,409 --> 01:43:28,577
I got him!

1244
01:43:28,661 --> 01:43:32,248
I finally got him!

1245
01:43:37,712 --> 01:43:39,463
What was that?

1246
01:44:25,342 --> 01:44:27,553
It's over, Eggman.

1247
01:44:28,929 --> 01:44:31,640
I like the new look. It works for you.

1248
01:44:32,224 --> 01:44:35,227
What do you say
we just let bygones be bygones?

1249
01:44:35,311 --> 01:44:39,064
I did some things, you did some things.
There are good people on both sides.

1250
01:44:40,775 --> 01:44:43,861
Surely two intelligent beings

1251
01:44:45,613 --> 01:44:47,615
can work these things out!

1252
01:44:59,627 --> 01:45:02,087
- Come on, buddy. Come on.
- Get him, Sonic!

1253
01:45:02,171 --> 01:45:03,506
Yeah. Come on.

1254
01:45:20,064 --> 01:45:21,524
It's like that?

1255
01:45:23,025 --> 01:45:25,319
Okay, we're not friends.

1256
01:45:29,740 --> 01:45:32,034
Later, hater!

1257
01:45:43,420 --> 01:45:44,880
- Sonic!
- Buddy!

1258
01:45:45,464 --> 01:45:47,508
Wait! You cannot touch him!

1259
01:45:47,591 --> 01:45:50,261
The hedgehog holds
the power of the Emerald.

1260
01:45:50,970 --> 01:45:54,557
I am sorry.
He is no longer the Sonic you once knew.

1261
01:45:55,140 --> 01:45:56,141
What?

1262
01:46:16,078 --> 01:46:17,705
You got to try this.

1263
01:46:23,460 --> 01:46:26,797
Okay.
He is exactly the Sonic you once knew.

1264
01:46:38,517 --> 01:46:39,602
Sonic!

1265
01:46:41,896 --> 01:46:43,480
Bring it in, bud.

1266
01:46:44,940 --> 01:46:46,901
It's good to be back in blue.

1267
01:46:46,984 --> 01:46:50,321
The golden god thing was fun,
but blue has always been more my color.

1268
01:46:50,404 --> 01:46:51,488
Looks good on you.

1269
01:46:51,572 --> 01:46:56,994
Sonic, you were the most powerful hero
in the universe, and you let it go.

1270
01:46:57,077 --> 01:46:58,162
Why?

1271
01:46:59,914 --> 01:47:03,042
Because I still have
some growing up to do.

1272
01:47:05,294 --> 01:47:09,048
- And I kind of like being a kid.
- And you're not just any kid.

1273
01:47:09,632 --> 01:47:11,508
You're our kid.

1274
01:47:11,592 --> 01:47:13,010
That's right.

1275
01:47:13,093 --> 01:47:15,804
- Bring it in!
- Yay. Hugs.

1276
01:47:15,888 --> 01:47:18,724
It's a good thing we didn't do this
before. You would've blown up.

1277
01:47:26,357 --> 01:47:27,942
You fixed it.

1278
01:47:28,025 --> 01:47:31,362
I've spent my whole life
questing for this.

1279
01:47:31,445 --> 01:47:32,738
Now I have it.

1280
01:47:32,821 --> 01:47:34,615
Now we have it.

1281
01:47:34,698 --> 01:47:37,284
What do we do with it? What next?

1282
01:47:37,368 --> 01:47:39,495
There were once two orders of heroes

1283
01:47:39,578 --> 01:47:43,707
who protected the galaxy from those
who would use the Emerald for evil.

1284
01:47:43,791 --> 01:47:47,670
But they have all passed on
to the great battleground in the sky.

1285
01:47:47,753 --> 01:47:51,215
So we start a new order. The three of us.

1286
01:47:51,298 --> 01:47:53,008
This is no light task.

1287
01:47:53,092 --> 01:47:57,721
We must make a vow to use our powers
to keep the universe safe,

1288
01:47:58,555 --> 01:48:00,391
to watch out for each other.

1289
01:48:00,474 --> 01:48:02,184
Our new tribe.

1290
01:48:02,267 --> 01:48:03,394
I know!

1291
01:48:03,477 --> 01:48:05,896
- A power bump!
- Good idea.

1292
01:48:06,939 --> 01:48:10,150
It's an Earth custom.
An unbreakable promise.

1293
01:48:10,734 --> 01:48:12,027
Very well.

1294
01:48:12,820 --> 01:48:15,239
A power bump it is.

1295
01:48:16,407 --> 01:48:18,075
Power bump!

1296
01:48:21,996 --> 01:48:26,125
It's truly a beautiful day for baseball
here in Green Hills.

1297
01:48:26,208 --> 01:48:27,918
An exciting lineup today

1298
01:48:28,002 --> 01:48:31,296
with the debut appearance
of two new players!

1299
01:48:31,380 --> 01:48:35,551
On the mound,
rookie sensation from across the galaxy,

1300
01:48:35,634 --> 01:48:38,178
Miles "Tails" Prower,

1301
01:48:38,262 --> 01:48:42,975
facing off against the powerhouse,
Knuckles the Echidna.

1302
01:48:44,435 --> 01:48:46,311
I don't understand.

1303
01:48:46,395 --> 01:48:48,564
Why am I angry at the enemy ball?

1304
01:48:48,647 --> 01:48:49,815
You're not angry.

1305
01:48:49,898 --> 01:48:53,152
You just want to hit it as hard as you can
and then run around the bases.

1306
01:48:53,235 --> 01:48:57,865
But if my quest ends where I am standing,
why run at all?

1307
01:48:58,532 --> 01:49:01,076
I can't with this guy. Why do I even try?

1308
01:49:01,160 --> 01:49:03,829
This is just a game.
We're out here having fun.

1309
01:49:03,912 --> 01:49:05,414
Just having some fun.

1310
01:49:05,497 --> 01:49:06,915
Fun.

1311
01:49:08,125 --> 01:49:10,502
All right! Give him the heat, Tails!

1312
01:49:10,586 --> 01:49:12,504
Hope you're ready for my fastball.

1313
01:49:12,588 --> 01:49:15,049
Your fastball will be dishonored.

1314
01:49:15,132 --> 01:49:17,384
And so will you, fox.

1315
01:49:17,468 --> 01:49:19,845
- Easy, guys!
- Don't think about it too much.

1316
01:49:19,928 --> 01:49:23,348
Just keep your elbow up,
eye on the ball and give it a ride.

1317
01:49:23,432 --> 01:49:24,850
A ride? To where?

1318
01:49:29,104 --> 01:49:30,397
Power bump!

1319
01:49:35,694 --> 01:49:37,154
Victory is mine!

1320
01:49:37,237 --> 01:49:39,782
Hey, no fair! That shouldn't count.

1321
01:49:39,865 --> 01:49:42,117
First base is also mine!

1322
01:49:42,201 --> 01:49:46,789
- I think that was our only ball.
- I have conquered the second of the bases!

1323
01:49:46,872 --> 01:49:48,415
Who wants ice cream?

1324
01:49:48,499 --> 01:49:49,708
Knocked the cover off that.

1325
01:49:49,792 --> 01:49:51,710
- Ice cream!
- Ice cream, yeah!

1326
01:49:52,961 --> 01:49:56,423
I am having the fun! What is ice cream?

1327
01:49:56,507 --> 01:49:59,843
It's a dessert.
If you like fun, you're gonna love it.

1328
01:49:59,927 --> 01:50:03,097
Yum. Dessert. Does it have grapes in it?

1329
01:50:03,180 --> 01:50:04,765
No, not usually.

1330
01:50:04,848 --> 01:50:06,517
I'm proud of our little guy.

1331
01:50:07,392 --> 01:50:10,437
I really like his new friends,
especially the red one.

1332
01:50:10,938 --> 01:50:13,565
- He cracks me up.
- Heck of a swing too.

1333
01:50:13,649 --> 01:50:16,401
Come on, fox.
Our dessert adventure awaits.

1334
01:50:16,485 --> 01:50:17,820
- Good job, guys.
- Yeah.

1335
01:50:17,903 --> 01:50:21,198
You too, baby. Let's go get
some ice cream. Come on, come on.

1336
01:50:22,366 --> 01:50:24,535
I'm happy for you, pal.

1337
01:50:24,618 --> 01:50:27,788
Got your wingmen.
Perfect friends to grow up with.

1338
01:50:27,871 --> 01:50:31,166
- Come on, Knuckles.
- My victory chariot!

1339
01:50:33,210 --> 01:50:36,171
I've got a lot more than that... Dad.

1340
01:50:41,635 --> 01:50:42,970
Race you to the truck.

1341
01:50:44,638 --> 01:50:46,056
One, two, three, go!

1342
01:50:46,640 --> 01:50:48,767
No, don't go easy on me. I want your best.

1343
01:50:48,851 --> 01:50:51,812
Sonic, I have just been told
they have sprinkles.

1344
01:50:51,895 --> 01:50:55,566
Ice cream and sprinkles?
This is your new destiny.

1345
01:50:55,649 --> 01:51:00,571
What a perfect meal to celebrate
my victory over you in base of ball.

1346
01:51:00,654 --> 01:51:03,282
- What?
- I mean, you barely beat me.

1347
01:51:03,949 --> 01:51:06,451
You've never been beaten so hard.

1348
01:51:10,873 --> 01:51:12,040
Can't forget this.

1349
01:53:11,410 --> 01:53:13,287
Agent, I want an update.

1350
01:53:13,370 --> 01:53:16,290
Still searching, sir.
We haven't found any sign of Robotnik.

1351
01:53:16,373 --> 01:53:18,709
No one could've survived that crash.

1352
01:53:18,792 --> 01:53:21,378
He's toast. Good riddance.

1353
01:53:21,962 --> 01:53:24,715
What a mess that lunatic made.

1354
01:53:25,299 --> 01:53:28,176
Sir, there's something else.

1355
01:53:28,719 --> 01:53:32,222
When we were wiping Robotnik
off our database, we found something.

1356
01:53:32,306 --> 01:53:36,059
A file buried deep in our system
and dating back over 50 years.

1357
01:53:36,143 --> 01:53:39,062
- What was it?
- Coordinates, sir.

1358
01:53:39,146 --> 01:53:41,023
Coordinates? To what?

1359
01:53:41,773 --> 01:53:43,734
A secret research facility.

1360
01:53:44,359 --> 01:53:45,944
It was a black site, sir.

1361
01:53:46,695 --> 01:53:49,156
Someone worked very hard
to keep this hidden.

1362
01:53:50,532 --> 01:53:51,742
My God.

1363
01:53:52,701 --> 01:53:54,036
Project Shadow.

